Using the `virtctl`, OpenShift Virtualization can export VMs and their associated disks to import them into another OpenShift Virtualization cluster.


### Exporting a VM

```bash
cat > export-fedora-vm.yaml
```

```yaml
apiVersion: export.kubevirt.io/v1beta1
kind: VirtualMachineExport
metadata:
  name: fedora-export
  namespace: vms
spec:
  source:
    apiGroup: "kubevirt.io"
    kind: VirtualMachine
    name: fedora-vm
  ttlDuration: 1h
```

